The '''Runaway Droid Ride''' was a well-known escape made by a [[Starship/Legends|ship]] filled with droids. A [[3PO-series protocol droid/Legends|3PO-series]] [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol]] [[Droid/Legends|droid]] named [[Squeaky (droid)|Squeaky]] programmed the [[Autopilot/Legends|autopilot]] of a stolen [[Kessel/Legends|Kessel]] vessel, due to his inability to pilot a vehicle. This was intended to whisk the droids to freedom.

Unfortunately for him and the droids, Squeaky had forgotten that the autopilot employed a terrain-following system. The direction the craft started was full of hills, valleys, craters, and cliffs. Even with the less-than-pleasant journey, and to the surprise of a dazed Squeaky, the droids managed to escape the [[Potato/Legends|potato]]-shaped [[Planet/Legends|planet]].

After, Squeaky became very famous throughout different groups. He ended up serving the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], becoming [[Wraith Squadron]]'s [[Quartermaster/Legends|quartermaster]] and serving in the [[DownTime]] [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]].

